The paper discusses the performance of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) in terms of their ability to compress past information while being informative about the future. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, given that the paper focuses on RNNs and their optimization, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories.
